<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 6:58AM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Daniels
and northern Valley Counties through 800 AM MDT...
At 657 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Opheim, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Opheim, Richland, Port Of Opheim, Thoeny, Baylor and Glentana.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
